<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    This file contains some terms like default titles etc. used in eLML.
    Some of these terms are only used when the "title" attribute is missing,
    others are used only for the PDF version etc. 
    
    The structure of this file is based on the Google Gadgets API Developer Guide: 
    http://www.google.com/apis/gadgets/i18n.html
    
    The possible fields you can include in a terms file are as follows:
    - messagebundle: A group of messages for translation.
    - msg: A single piece of translatable content (title, sentence etc.)
    - name attribute: A human-readable ID for each term (the key of the term)
    (Please note that there is a corresponding XSLT variable for each name.
    So for the name attribute "name_entry" there is a variable $name_entry
    that can be used within the XSLT code for the title of an entry element.)
    
    There is one terms xml file per language (and country - but this is not used 
    in eLML at the moment). By convention these files are named as follows:
    terms_<language>_<country>.xml
    Since <country> is not used at the moment, just use "ALL". The default terms
    file is the English (fallback if language is not available) and it is named:
    terms_en_ALL.xml
    
-->
